 field team earned four All-Big 12 honors at the 2026 Big 12 Conference Outdoor Championships in Tucson, Arizona.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/17/IMG_3350.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/17/IMG_3350.jpeg"><media:title>Joy Naukot competing in the 10,000m meters at the Big 12 Outdoor Championships</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/17/IMG_3350.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 17 May 2026 00:14:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>16</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59108</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Rally to Defeat TCU in Regular Season Finale</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/16/baseball-mountaineers-rally-to-defeat-tcu-in-regular-season-finale</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/16/baseball-mountaineers-rally-to-defeat-tcu-in-regular-season-finale</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Brodie Kresser celebrates after hitting a double against TCU" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/16/G3_KU-146.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 9 West Virginia University baseball team defeated TCU, 6-4, Saturday afternoon at Kendrick Family Ballpark to conclude the regular season. The Mountaineers improve to 37-13 and 21-9 in the Big 12 while the Horned Frogs fall to 33-20 and 17-13 in conference play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/16/G3_KU-146.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/16/G3_KU-146.jpg"><media:title>Brodie Kresser celebrates after hitting a double against TCU</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/16/G3_KU-146.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 16 May 2026 16:54:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59107</s:story_id></item><item><title>Rowing Returns to Sarasota for Big 12 Championship</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/16/rowing-returns-to-sarasota-for-big-12-championship</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/16/rowing-returns-to-sarasota-for-big-12-championship</guid><category>Rowing</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="A graphic preview the 2026 Big 12 Rowing Championship" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/16/ROW26_RaceDay_Big12_1920X1080.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University rowing team will compete at the 2026 Big 12 Championship on Sunday, May 17, at Nathan Benderson Park in Sarasota, Florida.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/16/ROW26_RaceDay_Big12_1920X1080.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/16/ROW26_RaceDay_Big12_1920X1080.jpg"><media:title>A graphic preview the 2026 Big 12 Rowing Championship</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/16/ROW26_RaceDay_Big12_1920X1080.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 16 May 2026 10:50:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>12</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59106</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Drops Game Two to TCU</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/15/baseball-west-virginia-drops-game-two-to-tcu</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/15/baseball-west-virginia-drops-game-two-to-tcu</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Maxx Yehl throws a pitch against TCU" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/15/baseball5-15.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 9 West Virginia University baseball team fell to TCU, 4-0, Friday night at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers fall to 36-13 and 20-9 in the Big 12 while the Horned Frogs improve to 33-19 and 17-12 in league play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/15/baseball5-15.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/15/baseball5-15.jpg"><media:title>Maxx Yehl throws a pitch against TCU</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/15/baseball5-15.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 22:58:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59105</s:story_id></item></channel></rss>